notes.en: A lo-fi jazz foundry for city girls and boys (from IG bio). Located in Euljiro (Hipjiro) and known as a jazz bar. The name 'ê¸°ì›' (Giwon) means both 'origin/source' and 'Go parlor,' as the space was a Go parlor 30 years ago. Operated by jazz record producer and musician Kang Woong and expert partners. Shares a floor with 'í™”ë‹´' (@hwadam_winebar). On weekdays, plays modern jazz on vinyl, with music selection influenced by guests' atmosphere. Wine list consists of approximately 80% natural wines, with a progressive selection. Weekly Saturday performances are held, booked via Instagram DM. Performance schedule is announced 1 week in advance via Instagram, or a month in advance for direct visitors. The owner is a record collector and generally does not take song requests.
